---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Dashboard OS"
  description="The operating system behind Editorial Intelligence — how signals become insights, insights become frameworks, and frameworks become published work."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">The operating system</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Dashboard OS</h1>
        <p class="t-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Where do all these frameworks come from?
        </p>
        <p class="t-body mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-tertiary)">
          This page explains the repeatable system behind Editorial Intelligence — not a collection of tools, but a knowledge operating system for turning information into insight, strategy and published work.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- The operating system -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">The operating system</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-10">
          <p>Most content work resets with every project. A research report gets published. A brief lands. The cycle starts again.</p>
          <p>Dashboard OS is built on a different assumption: that every piece of information — a practitioner conversation, a survey finding, a market observation, a published article — has the potential to strengthen everything connected to it.</p>
          <p>The operating system captures that information continuously, organises it into connected knowledge, develops it into frameworks, and feeds the evidence generated by publication back into the system.</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-[var(--color-ink)]">It is designed to compound rather than reset.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The cycle flow -->
        <div class="os-flow">
          {[
            {
              step: 'Capture',
              desc: 'Signals arrive continuously — from events, research, customer conversations, market observations, published articles. The first job is to catch them before they disappear.',
            },
            {
              step: 'Organise',
              desc: 'Raw signals become structured knowledge. Notes become tagged observations. Observations connect to existing frameworks and narratives. Patterns begin to emerge.',
            },
            {
              step: 'Develop',
              desc: 'Where patterns converge, frameworks form. This is the editorial judgement layer — deciding what the signals are actually saying, what argument they support, and what can be made reusable from them.',
            },
            {
              step: 'Activate',
              desc: 'Developed ideas move into published work — articles, essays, frameworks, diagnostics, case studies, experiments. Each piece expresses part of the underlying knowledge system.',
            },
            {
              step: 'Measure',
              desc: 'Published work generates new evidence — what resonated, what questions it raised, what conversations it started. Not just traffic, but signal.',
            },
            {
              step: 'Learn',
              desc: 'Evidence from publication is interpreted editorially. What did the audience respond to? What does that reveal about the narrative? What needs strengthening?',
            },
            {
              step: 'Feed back',
              desc: 'Learning re-enters the system as new signal. The framework is refined. The narrative gets stronger. The next piece starts from a higher base than the last.',
            },
          ].map((item, i) => (
            <div class="os-flow-step">
              <div class="os-flow-content">
                <div class="os-flow-header">
                  <span class="os-flow-number">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
                  <span class="os-flow-step-label">{item.step}</span>
                </div>
                <p class="os-flow-desc">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
              {i < 6 && <div class="os-flow-arrow">↓</div>}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Dashboard layers -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">The four layers</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-10">
          <p>The operating system runs across four interconnected layers. Each has a distinct purpose. Together they form a system where information moves from raw capture to published knowledge.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="layer-stack">

          <!-- Layer 1: Daily OS -->
          <div class="layer-card">
            <div class="layer-card-header">
              <span class="layer-number">01</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="layer-title">Daily OS</h3>
                <p class="layer-purpose">Manage execution and maintain momentum</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="layer-desc">The operational layer. Not strategy — execution. This is where priorities are set, projects are tracked and the weekly review happens. It exists to protect the strategic work from being crowded out by immediate demands.</p>
            <div class="layer-elements">
              {['Priorities', 'Sprint planning', 'Weekly review', 'Active projects', 'Work-life balance', 'Habits'].map((el) => (
                <span class="layer-element">{el}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Layer 2: EI Dashboard -->
          <div class="layer-card layer-card--featured">
            <div class="layer-card-header">
              <span class="layer-number">02</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="layer-title">Editorial Intelligence Dashboard</h3>
                <p class="layer-purpose">Turn signals into connected editorial knowledge</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="layer-desc">The strategic core. This is where signals from research, events, customer conversations and market observations are captured, organised and connected. It is where frameworks develop and narratives take shape — before anything is published.</p>
            <div class="layer-elements">
              {['Customer research', 'Practitioner conversations', 'Market signals', 'Framework development', 'Evidence library', 'Narrative mapping', 'Content opportunities'].map((el) => (
                <span class="layer-element">{el}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Layer 3: EI Lab -->
          <div class="layer-card">
            <div class="layer-card-header">
              <span class="layer-number">03</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="layer-title">Editorial Intelligence Lab</h3>
                <p class="layer-purpose">Experiment before publication</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="layer-desc">The testing layer. Ideas that aren't ready for publication live here — AI workflows under development, prototype frameworks, diagnostic tools being stress-tested, editorial experiments. The Lab is where ideas earn the right to become frameworks.</p>
            <div class="layer-elements">
              {['AI workflows', 'Prompt libraries', 'Prototype frameworks', 'Diagnostics', 'Experiments', 'Editorial testing'].map((el) => (
                <span class="layer-element">{el}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Layer 4: Public knowledge -->
          <div class="layer-card layer-card--public">
            <div class="layer-card-header">
              <span class="layer-number">04</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="layer-title">Public knowledge</h3>
                <p class="layer-purpose">Ideas developed enough to share</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="layer-desc">Once an idea has been tested, refined and stress-tested against real evidence, it moves into the public layer — this site. Publication is not the end of the process. Each published piece generates new evidence that feeds back into the system.</p>
            <div class="layer-elements">
              {['Frameworks', 'Models', 'Articles', 'Essays', 'Case studies', 'Presentations'].map((el) => (
                <span class="layer-element">{el}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
            <a href="/" class="layer-link">Explore the public layer →</a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Key principles -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Key principles</h2>
        <div class="principles-stack">
          {[
            {
              principle: 'Information becomes knowledge when it is connected.',
              expansion: 'A signal in isolation is just a data point. Connected to other signals from different sources, it reveals a pattern. The operating system is designed to make connection the default, not an occasional practice.',
            },
            {
              principle: 'Knowledge becomes strategy when patterns emerge.',
              expansion: 'Not every pattern is strategic. The editorial judgement required here is distinguishing a genuine through-line — something that holds across multiple sources and over time — from a coincidence.',
            },
            {
              principle: 'Strategy becomes value when ideas are activated through content.',
              expansion: 'A framework that stays private has no leverage. The point of the system is to move ideas from internal capture to external expression — and in doing so, to test them against a real audience.',
            },
            {
              principle: 'Every published asset generates new evidence for the system.',
              expansion: 'Publication is not the end of the process. What the audience responds to, what questions they ask, what they share — all of this is signal. The system feeds on its own output.',
            },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="principle-card">
              <p class="principle-statement">"{item.principle}"</p>
              <p class="principle-expansion">{item.expansion}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What this produces -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">What this produces</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Editorial Intelligence is not simply a collection of articles. It is a repeatable system for transforming research, customer insight and market signals into reusable editorial assets, strategic frameworks and organisational knowledge.</p>
          <p>The frameworks on this site — <a href="/frameworks/editorial-intelligence-framework" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Editorial Intelligence</a>, <a href="/frameworks/ai-maturity-curve" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">AI Maturity Curve</a>, <a href="/frameworks/customer-signal-framework" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Customer Signal Framework</a> — came through this system. So did the narratives: <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Hidden Hours</a>, <a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Winning in Small</a>, <a href="/narratives/expanding-cfo" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">The Expanding CFO</a>.</p>
          <p>Each one began as a signal. The operating system is what turned it into something reusable.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  /* OS Flow */
  .os-flow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .os-flow-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .os-flow-content {
    padding: 1.125rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .os-flow-step:last-child .os-flow-content {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, var(--color-surface));
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .os-flow-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .os-flow-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .os-flow-step-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .os-flow-step:last-child .os-flow-step-label {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .os-flow-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    padding-left: 1.75rem;
  }

  .os-flow-arrow {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  /* Layer stack */
  .layer-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .layer-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .layer-card--featured {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 5%, var(--color-surface));
  }

  .layer-card--public {
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .layer-card-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .layer-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .layer-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .layer-purpose {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .layer-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .layer-elements {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .layer-element {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .layer-card--featured .layer-element {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, var(--color-surface));
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 20%, transparent);
  }

  .layer-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .layer-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Principles */
  .principles-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .principle-card {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.625rem;
  }

  .principle-card:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .principle-statement {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.5;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .principle-expansion {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
  }
</style>
